d precursor chemistry emphasized in the report."}, {"id": "rxn_021", "name": "Mineral-assisted reductive amination/transformation from pyruvate network toward serine", "inputs": ["mol_021", "mol_006", "mol_004"], "outputs": ["mol_015"], "environment": "Hydrothermal", "agents": ["pyrite", "magnetite"], "conditions": {"temperature": "353-423K", "pressure": "high", "catalyst": "iron-sulfur mineral surfaces", "aqueous": "true", "other": "network-level amino acid generation from central alpha-keto acids; partially speculative connector"}, "mechanism": "Hydrothermal amino-acid-forming chemistry converts alpha-keto acid feedstocks and C1 carbon into oxygenated amino acids including serine.", "reasoning": "The report emphasizes hydrothermal production of pyruvate and amino acids on mineral surfaces, while Hennet, Holm & Engel (1992) directly observed serine in mineral-catalyzed hydrothermal reactions. This connector is somewhat schematic but literature-consistent and provides a bridge between hydrothermal alpha-keto acid chemistry and serine availability."}, {"id": "rxn_022", "name": "Conversion of serine to serine nitrile in mixed nitrile-rich surface pools", "inputs": ["mol_015", "mol_003"], "outputs": ["mol_007"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["montmorillonite (clay)", "phosphate minerals (apatite, struvite)"], "conditions": {"temperature": "300-330K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "concentration and exchange on mineral surfaces", "aqueous": "true", "other": "nitrile-rich evaporitic pool; speculative back-conversion"}, "mechanism": "In nitrile-rich settings, serine can be integrated into aminonitrile pools feeding the biomimetic cysteine sequence.", "reasoning": "This connector is speculative but serves to join hydrothermal serine production with the experimentally established serine nitrile-centered pathway of Foden et al. (2020). It does not contradict the literature and reflects the report's emphasis on environmental integration and feedstock exchange across